MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 13.6 (patch 0022) hardcoded RING_BUFFER_CHUNKS=16 to fix audio chop
on PODP 5V83. That introduced a keyboard regression on real HW (frozen
keyboard input after engine startup, 8042 buffer-overflow beep on
keypress). See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §2.

This patch makes wave 13.6 bisectable in a single CF-card swap:

1. SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS=4|8|16 toggles the audio ring
   depth at runtime. Default = 16 (matches wave 13.6 behaviour with no
   env vars set; the regression is intentionally still in the default —
   this slot is for diagnosis, not a pre-emptive fix). Strict-match
   parsing per the project convention: anything other than the exact
   strings "4", "8", "16" → 16. Cached on first OpenDevice call so
   re-entry never re-reads the env. resolve_ring_chunks() also exports
   the resolved value to a linkage-visible int
   doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active that the engine's phase-timing log
   reads — single source of truth, avoids engine-side parser drift.

2. IRQ-delivery counters doskutsu_kbd_irq_count and
   doskutsu_kbd_drain_count (volatile uint32_t, DOS_LockVariable'd)
   bumped from KeyboardIRQHandler and DOSVESA_PumpEvents drain loop
   respectively. Engine's phase-timing log block reads both via extern
   declarations. Locked with DOS_LockVariable since they're read across
   IRQ/main-thread context. If the kbd freeze on g2k coincides with
   irq_count plateauing → DPMI/scheduler problem; if irq_count keeps
   climbing but drain_count falls behind → game-thread starvation.

3. New SDL_Log line at OpenDevice records the active ring_chunks,
   chunk_size, ring_size, and the raw env-var string (or "(unset)") so
   each DEBUG.LOG run self-describes which audio config it ran with.

Default behaviour unchanged from wave 13.6 when no env vars are set.
Pairs with engine-side patch 0068 (Renderer.cpp phase-timing log
extension + ring-chunks init banner).

See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §2 for the full bisect plan.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c | 78 +++++++++++++++++++++++++--------
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c   | 27 ++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 87 insertions(+), 18 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c b/src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c
index eb3e50b2c..327260a8b 100644
--- a/src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c
+++ b/src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c
@@ -85,22 +85,51 @@ static Uint8 ReadSoundBlasterDSP(void)
 // (using the full SDL pipeline with all its allocations and mutexes), and
 // the ISR just does a memcpy (no SDL calls, no DPMI, no allocator).
 
-// Number of DMA half-buffers that fit in the ring. Must be a power of two.
-// 4 chunks is ~45 ms at 44100 Hz, enough headroom for 22 fps frame times.
-/* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6): bump from 4 to 16 chunks. With
-   SDL3's default sample_frames=512 (2048-byte chunks at 22050 stereo S16),
-   16 chunks = 32 KB = 372 ms of buffer. Wave 13.5 real-HW measurements
-   (PODP 5V83) showed bigger sample_frames is SLOWER per-flip (cache
-   pressure on the P54C's 8 KB L1 D-cache when chunk memcpy ≥ 8 KB), so
-   we keep small chunks for speed but use a deeper ring to avoid audio
-   underrun in slow scenes (cmod-heavy menus drop to ~2 fps = 500 ms
-   between game-yields → buffer needs ≥500 ms to never miss). 372 ms is
-   not enough for the worst-case 500 ms cmod-menu gap but covers the
-   common 10 fps title scene with margin and dramatically improves the
-   chop frequency vs the 92 ms of the original 4-chunk ring. Memory
-   cost: 32 KB ring + 2 KB staging vs 8 KB ring + 2 KB staging — 24 KB
-   extra, trivial against 48 MB XMS budget. */
-#define RING_BUFFER_CHUNKS 16
+// Number of DMA half-buffers that fit in the ring. Must be a power of two
+// (we accept 4, 8, 16). Resolved from SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS;
+// see resolve_ring_chunks() below.
+//
+// DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): wave 13.6 hardcoded this to 16
+// (372 ms buffer at 22050 Hz stereo S16, default chunk_size 2048 B) to
+// fix audio chop on PODP 5V83. That introduced a keyboard regression
+// — see docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §2. Wave 13.6.1 makes the value
+// runtime-overridable so the regression can be bisected in a single
+// CF-card swap by setting:
+//   SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS=4   (8 KB ring, 92 ms — wave 13.5 baseline)
+//   SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS=8   (16 KB ring, 184 ms — intermediate)
+//   SET SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS=16  (32 KB ring, 372 ms — wave 13.6 default)
+// Default (unset / unrecognized) = 16 to match wave 13.6 behaviour
+// when no env vars are set.
+//
+// EXPORTED: doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active is read by the engine's
+// phase-timing log block (Renderer.cpp). Single source of truth.
+
+/* doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active: linkage-visible to engine. Set on
+   the first call to resolve_ring_chunks(). Reads default to 16 if the
+   audio device has not been opened yet. */
+int doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active = 16;
+
+static int resolve_ring_chunks(void)
+{
+    static int cached = -1;
+    if (cached == -1) {
+        const char *e = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS");
+        int v = 16; /* default — matches wave 13.6 behaviour */
+        if (e) {
+            if (e[0] == '4' && e[1] == 0) {
+                v = 4;
+            } else if (e[0] == '8' && e[1] == 0) {
+                v = 8;
+            } else if (e[0] == '1' && e[1] == '6' && e[2] == 0) {
+                v = 16;
+            }
+            /* else: keep default 16 */
+        }
+        cached = v;
+        doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active = v;
+    }
+    return cached;
+}
 
 // All of the following statics are memory-locked, making them safe to access
 // from the ISR without risking a page fault or DPMI re-entrance.
@@ -313,8 +342,10 @@ static bool DOSSOUNDBLASTER_OpenDevice(SDL_AudioDevice *device)
     // Set up the IRQ-driven ring buffer.
     hidden->chunk_size = device->buffer_size; // one DMA half-buffer
 
-    // Ring size must be a power of two and hold RING_BUFFER_CHUNKS chunks.
-    hidden->ring_size = hidden->chunk_size * RING_BUFFER_CHUNKS;
+    // Ring size must be a power of two and hold N chunks, N resolved
+    // from SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS (4/8/16, default 16).
+    const int ring_chunks = resolve_ring_chunks();
+    hidden->ring_size = hidden->chunk_size * ring_chunks;
     // Ensure power-of-two (chunk_size itself comes from SDL and may not be).
     {
         int rs = hidden->ring_size;
@@ -337,6 +368,17 @@ static bool DOSSOUNDBLASTER_OpenDevice(SDL_AudioDevice *device)
         return SDL_SetError("Couldn't allocate staging buffer for IRQ-driven audio");
     }
 
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): log the active ring-chunks
+       value alongside the resolved ring_size and chunk_size so a single
+       DEBUG.LOG line tells us which audio config a run used. */
+    {
+        const char *env = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS");
+        SDL_Log("SOUNDBLASTER: ring_chunks=%d chunk_size=%d ring_size=%d (env "
+                "SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS=%s)",
+                ring_chunks, hidden->chunk_size, hidden->ring_size,
+                env ? env : "(unset)");
+    }
+
     hidden->ring_read = 0;
     hidden->ring_write = 0;
 
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
index 22906c6b6..912da585b 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
@@ -252,6 +252,24 @@ static Uint8 keyevents_ringbuffer[256];
 static int keyevents_head = 0;
 static int keyevents_tail = 0;
 
+/* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): IRQ-delivery counters for the
+   keyboard regression bisect. These are bumped:
+     - kbd_irq_count: in KeyboardIRQHandler, once per IRQ-1 fire. If
+       this stops incrementing during the freeze, IRQ delivery is
+       dead → DPMI-side problem (audio thread / scheduler hogging).
+     - kbd_drain_count: in DOSVESA_PumpEvents, once per byte drained
+       from keyevents_ringbuffer. If kbd_irq keeps incrementing but
+       drain falls behind, pump scheduling is the bottleneck →
+       game-thread starvation.
+   Both visible to engine via extern declarations in Renderer.cpp.
+   Both DOS_LockVariable'd: kbd_irq_count is updated from IRQ
+   context and must be locked. kbd_drain_count is bumped from the
+   main thread BUT torn-read from IRQ context isn't impossible
+   (engine thread reading via extern, IRQ firing) — the lock costs
+   nothing once and avoids reasoning about atomicity. Lock both. */
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_count = 0;
+volatile uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_drain_count = 0;
+
 void DOSVESA_PumpEvents(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
 {
     /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.3): the per-pump DOS_Yield() was
@@ -278,6 +296,9 @@ void DOSVESA_PumpEvents(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
     while (keyevents_head != keyevents_tail) {
         const Uint8 event = keyevents_ringbuffer[keyevents_tail];
         keyevents_tail = (keyevents_tail + 1) & (SDL_arraysize(keyevents_ringbuffer) - 1);
+        /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): drain-rate counter
+           for keyboard-regression bisect. */
+        doskutsu_kbd_drain_count++;
 
         // Handle remaining bytes of E1 Pause key sequence (E1 1D 45 E1 9D C5).
         if (pause_sequence_remaining > 0) {
@@ -366,6 +387,9 @@ void DOSVESA_PumpEvents(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
 
 static void KeyboardIRQHandler(void) // this is wrapped in a thing that handles IRET, etc.
 {
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): IRQ-fire counter for
+       keyboard-regression bisect. Read by engine's phase-timing log. */
+    doskutsu_kbd_irq_count++;
     keyevents_ringbuffer[keyevents_head] = inportb(KBD_DATA_PORT);
     keyevents_head = (keyevents_head + 1) & (SDL_arraysize(keyevents_ringbuffer) - 1);
     DOS_EndOfInterrupt(1);
@@ -381,6 +405,9 @@ void DOSVESA_InitKeyboard(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
     DOS_LockVariable(keyevents_ringbuffer);
     DOS_LockVariable(keyevents_head);
     DOS_LockVariable(keyevents_tail);
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): IRQ-bisect counters. */
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_irq_count);
+    DOS_LockVariable(doskutsu_kbd_drain_count);
 
     DOS_HookInterrupt(1, KeyboardIRQHandler, &data->keyboard_interrupt_hook);
 }
